<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
		xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
		xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
		>
<head>
	<title>{% block title %}{{title}} - {{titleleaf}}{% endblock %}</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" media="screen" href="css/default.css" />
</head>
<body onload="beginModernBrowsing( document.getElementById( 'beginmodernbrowsing' ), document.getElementById( 'modernbrowsermessage' ) );">
<div id="beginmodernbrowsing">
	<div id="modernbrowsermessage">
		<div>
			If you see this text, and nothing else,
			then perhaps trying a modern browser would
			allow you to view the exciting logo that
			should be appearing as this text fades away...
		</div>
		<div>
			The lightcrud module is a lightweight, potentially
			insecure way to publish Models via a CRUD-centric
			RESTful API.
		</div>
		<div>
			For example,
			/Crud/ModelName/ to create,
			/cRud/ to read,
			/crUd/ModelName/id to update,
			and /cruD/ModelName/id to delete.
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
<script type="text/javascript" media="screen" src="js/default.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" media="screen" src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.3.2/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" media="screen" src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jqueryui/1.7.2/jquery-ui.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
